The Data Management Tool (DMT) 2018 was created to manage data entry, transfer and control of
information collected in the field, in the scope of the LUCAS 2018 survey.
This architecture allows the collection of information (data entry at surveyor level) and the
centralization of information in a single database (ORACLE) stored on a remote server (hosted
platform).
